President Biden and Vice President Harris met with Senators and House members who have been leaders in immigration reform. They discussed their support for Dreamers and the actions the Administration is taking to protect them and allow them to stay in the US. They expressed strong support for including immigration reform in upcoming legislation to provide pathways to citizenship for Dreamers, TPS recipients, farmworkers, and essential workers. The lawmakers thanked the Administration for their commitment to immigration reform and establishing a fair and humane immigration system.